============================================================================
Please consider to contribute and participate in an

Academic Globalization Project: Call for abstracts/articles and participation. http://www.iiis-cyber.org/wmsci2007/ag.asp

and/or in Info-CybernEthics 2007: Call for abstracts/articles and participation: http://www.iiis-cyber.org/wmsci2007/ice.asp
============================================================================
Deadlines for both:

Submissions:  May 25th, 2007
Acceptance notification: A maximum of 10 days after submission's date
Camera-ready for Pre-Conference Proceedings: June 10th, 2007
Camera-ready for the Post-Conference volume of the Proceedings: July 12th, 2007.
============================================================================
The Academic Globalization Project would include plenary keynote addresses, structured and non-structured conversational face-to-face sessions, electronic sessions, e-conferences, virtual and/or face-to-face panels, 3 kinds of publications (hard copy proceedings, CD proceedings, Web) and 4-5 publication for best articles, which will also be published in a multiple-author book and/or in the JSCI journal.

These events will be linked to each other and their aggregated output would be input to 2008 events, and so on for next conferences, in an integrated multiple-year and multiple-event project.  More details about these events and their integrative links are provided at http://www.iiis-cyber.org/wmsci2007/ag.asp

Info-CybernEthics 2007 will include similar processes, products and publications, as well as the integrative links among them.
============================================================================
Please consider to distribute this email to appropriate colleagues and groups.

Thank you,
Conference Organizing Committee
